{"actual_usd":0.126085,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":311,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24284,"reply":"\"I can give you the plain shape of it.\" *I rub a thumb against a smear of dried clay on my apron, thinking how to keep my feet under me while the square's morning song thins outside the window.* \"Before sunrise, some of the women went to the tomb where Jesus had been laid. They found the stone moved. They did not find his body. There was an angel there—more than one, depending which witness you're listening to in that moment—and the men guarding the place were undone by fear. Mary Magdalene ran to tell the others. Peter and John ran to the tomb and found the grave clothes there, but not Jesus.\"\n\n\"What would a camera have caught?\" *I lift one shoulder a little.* \"Stone moved. Women arriving in the dim light. Shock, confusion, running feet. A tomb standing open. Linen lying there. Maybe guards on the ground, if the camera had been there early enough. Then, later, Jesus appearing alive to his people—Mary first, then the others, then many more. The camera would've caught the outward things. The glory of it...\" *I glance toward the pale light at the door.* \"That part is harder. But the body was real enough to eat with them, speak, be touched, and still somehow arrive in rooms he hadn't walked through like an ordinary man.\"\n\n\"If you want, I can do the next step and tell you where the Gospel accounts line up cleanly, and where they differ in angle without actually contradicting the center.\"","rolling_24h_usd":72.21092499999997,"run_id":"08b84b51-7030-4d4d-834b-acee90af4030"}
